<div class="about-content">
    <h2>About the 531 x 365 Program</h2>
    
    <p>The 531 x 365 program is a year-long training system that alternates between volume and intensity phases across 12 cycles. Originally designed by a lifter on Reddit, this program has helped thousands achieve significant strength gains.</p>
    
    <h3>Program Features</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>12-Cycle Structure:</strong> Alternating volume and intensity phases</li>
        <li><strong>5s PRO Main Sets:</strong> No AMRAP grinding, focus on quality reps</li>
        <li><strong>Progressive Overload:</strong> Training Max increases every cycle</li>
        <li><strong>Bodyweight Accessories:</strong> Complete training without extra equipment</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>How to Use</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Enter your current 1-rep maxes</li>
        <li>Select your current cycle and week</li>
        <li>Follow the calculated weights and accessories</li>
        <li>Progress through all 12 cycles</li>
        <li>Test new maxes and restart with higher numbers</li>
    </ol>
    
    <h3>Training Schedule</h3>
    <p>Follow a 4-day split:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Day 1:</strong> Overhead Press + Upper Accessories</li>
        <li><strong>Day 2:</strong> Squat + Lower Accessories</li>
        <li><strong>Day 3:</strong> Rest</li>
        <li><strong>Day 4:</strong> Bench Press + Upper Accessories</li>
        <li><strong>Day 5:</strong> Deadlift + Lower Accessories</li>
        <li><strong>Days 6-7:</strong> Rest</li>
    </ul>
</div>
